divs: sighting detailsmy wife and i were on assignment to take pictures of area cotton gins for a local business. we took the pictures on oct. 8,2008 at about 12:40 in the afternoon. when we loaded the images on the computer we noticed that one of them had an image on it that was not observed at the time of shooting. on closer examination we looked at the next image taken less than 5 seconds later and the object in question is not there. we have taken pictures professionally for ten years and do not have an explanation for what the object is. the attached image has not been altered in any way. the camera was a canon 5d with a 24-70l lens with a shutter speed of 1\200 of a second.
Summary: The object is cigar shaped with two fins on each side of the main bady.
